entry.title: SEKE Paper Submission
entry.content: Instead of pushing ahead to present my proposal, I’ve spent the last few weeks turning the proposal into a paper (available here on Github) for submission to the Conference on Software Engineering and Knowledge Engineering (SEKE 2015). This is something that I have never done before, so I’m very grateful that I had Dr. Anvik to co-author the paper with me. The paper would probably fit well into the Measurement and Empirical Software Engineering category. But, whether the paper is accepted or not, I appreciated the chance to experience the process. And we can always improve it and resubmit to another conference.
